                <h3>Main points</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>5-Year Performance:</strong> Bro Billionaire Stocks returned 850%+ vs S&P 500's 95%.
                        Concentration crushed diversification.</li>
                    <li><strong>The Paradox:</strong> S&P 500 is 30%+ Bro Stocks anyway. By buying SPY, you're diluting
                        the winners with 470 mediocre companies.</li>
                    <li><strong>Risk:</strong> Bro Stocks have 2x the volatility but higher quality (100% profitable vs
                        75% for S&P).</li>
                    <li><strong>Diversification Myth:</strong> S&P 500's "diversification" didn't protect in 2022â€”it
                        still dropped 25%. Just less than tech.</li>
                    <li><strong>Best Strategy:</strong> 60% S&P 500 (core) + 40% Bro Stocks overlay = capture upside
                        without excessive concentration risk.</li>
                    <li><strong>2026 Outlook:</strong> If AI continues, Bro Stocks win again. If market broadens, S&P
                        500 catches up via equal-weight outperformance.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
